The rule of law requiring the government to tell a (to "mirandize") suspect after arrest and before questioning that he has certain rights such as the right to remain silent, that the statements he makes may be used against him, his right to counsel and that counsel may be appointed if he cannot afford one. 

Source: [VA Journey Through Justice Glossary](http://www.jtj.courts.state.va.us/resources_glossary.html)